node.text:
It's World Mosquito Day!

Mosquito kills more than 700,000 people every year

Actually mosquito itself is not dangerous

But mosquito becomes carier of some deadly deseases

What we can prevent is to make the mosquitos breed less

Let's care more about the cleanliness in our home and environment

* Get rid of anything in your yard that could hold standing water (buckets, toys, tires)
* Pick up litter around your property
* Make sure screens/window-nets are in good repair so mosquitoes stay outside

From the pandemic nowadays, we also learn many things

DO NOT FEEL ASHAMED OF DOING THE RIGHT THING

We might look weird to wear a mask in our own home just because of a flu

We might look paranoid to wash hands every now and then

But if we can prevent the desease to spread, why not do what our hearts tell us to do?

Let's be cautious & mindful in every bits of our lives

Before our loved ones become the destruction of our wrong choices

We can do this together

@mingfulness presents:
* inspirational post every 1-3days
* animated video link in Bio/Profile every 2 weeks
.
.
.

Energy management

Hotels spend a lot of money on energy management, be it heating or air conditioning. Climate control is one of the most important aspects of the hospitality industry.
